Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Natural Language Inference (NLI) and language models. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for generating adversarial examples automatically. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses regularisation techniques for neural NLI models. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper deals with adversarial examples and improving the robustness of NLI models. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as the paper proposes a method for adversarially regularising neural NLI models.
